    "description": {
      "value": "<p>This ring is made from a glinting red metal and depicts flowers and growth.  Inside the band is an inscription written in Elvish.</p><p></p><p>While equipped and attuned, this ring grants the effect <strong>blooming.</strong></p><h2>Blooming Effect (Passive)</h2><p>While blooming is active, each time you cast a spell of <i>level 4 or below</i> there is a <strong>10% chance</strong> that the spell slot will be <strong>refunded instantly</strong>.</p><p>Additionally, each time the blooming effect triggers a flower spring from the ground near the ring bearer. If picked from the ground the flower will release <strong>4d4 + [level of spell] healing</strong> energy to the holder.</p><h3>Refund Last Spell Slot (Bonus Action)</h3><p>Once per day, you can forceably refund the last spell slot used, but this will suspend the <strong>blooming</strong> effect until the next dawn.</p>",
